<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="450" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">859B.01/194c: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Godthaab</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-27T21:00:00-04:00">May
                                        27, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>10. Our telegram No. 9, May 27, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>(1)</label>
                                <item>You may say to Governor Svane that we have been informed by
                                    Minister de Kauffmann that he not only approves of the
                                    transaction and believes its conclusion to be in the best
                                    interest of Greenland, but is prepared to sign the necessary
                                    documents and pay the purchase price of $10,000 from funds now
                                    available to him, immediately upon receipt through you of the
                                    authorization of the Greenland authorities.</item>
                                <label>(2)</label>
                                <item>Please tactfully attempt to expedite this matter as we wish to
                                    despatch the <hi rend="italic">Campbell</hi> to Greenland waters
                                    as soon as possible.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>